value.0: Sorry, <sir/madam>. Nobody is allowed into Blacklake. Very strict orders, you understand.
Yes, move along, <sir/madam>.
It's because we're keeping all the rabble such as yourself away. Now is there anything else?
Oh yeah? How about you just slink back to the academy and I'll forget you said that, little <man/woman>.
I don't care if you're Lord Bloody Nasher himself, and neither would Master Meldanen. You're not getting in.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Nice try. Meldanen has given me a description of unknowns that are allowed to enter and you don't match any of them.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Oh, is that right? You didn't quite match the description... In any case, the gate is open for you.
Ah, yes. Master Meldanen has been expecting you. You may enter the district and go to his estate. You can't miss it - it's at the end of the district and it's nearly as big as Castle Never itself.
A fair warning, if I may - although these gates are sealed to the public, his estate is not. It is fraught with dangerous experiments, minions, and other ilk.
Many have entered his estate and have never gotten past his ground floor. This shall also be your test - for if you cannot survive even that, then you will be of no use to Master Meldanen.
That is all I have been instructed to tell you. Would you like to enter the district now?
Very well, <sir/madam>.
Right this way, <sir/madam>.
I see that you've returned, <sir/madam>. Would you like to enter the district?
It's good to see someone from Blacklake. Would you like to enter the district?
I guess I'll be going, then.
Can you tell me why Blacklake doesn't seem to be affected by the Wailing Death?
You'll stand aside and let me enter, or it's your head.
I am a member of the city guard. I think I can enter.
<StartCheck>[Bluff]</Start> Didn't Meldanen tell you? He's sent for me.
I'm <FirstName>. I am sure Meldanen has told you of me.
I'll pass for now.
Yes.
